  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: cd20df6c9479f3d449851f4ca53de79e, type: 3}
  m_Name: GhostBook
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  bookTitle: Ghosts
  spreads:
  - layout: {fileID: 7412207408150843326, guid: d2c5a580268cc044da834634fe33a373, type: 3}
    textA: 'Here are my notes on different ghosts I have seen in the area.


      These
      are not ghosts in the way people often describe them.


      They observe.

      They
      react.


      And most importantly, they learn.'
    textB: 'There are at least three distinct manifestations that I have seen.


      I
      have stopped naming them.

      But if the temperature drops really fast,
      it''s most likely a spirit.'
    textC: 
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: 414262456008988909, guid: b6331614d4b599d479f493d5a48a67f0, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 6211519498159910813, guid: cc6383de98fd6294388821de6cde789f, type: 3}
    textA: Some apparitions recoil from certain wavelenghts. Not light, not exactly.
      Something harsher. This would explain why they don't come out during the day.
    textB: 'I exposed one to the UV inspection lamp. I''t didn''t vanish, it was
      destroyed. '
    textC: 
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: 414262456008988909, guid: b6331614d4b599d479f493d5a48a67f0, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 3671605574920047432, guid: 781c553c4079c4141a3d7fd57a077ce1, type: 3}
    textA: This could possibly be the ghost that keeps coming back, it would make
      sense as the ghost rides a horse....I don't know why it keeps coming back no
      matter how many times I destroy him with the UV light...
    textB: 
    textC: 
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: -6090594479009935761, guid: b0bdd106edc193a4c9510cfa29f6882d, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 2054620009573532433, guid: daad0ca62900cc64583361cbd74adb5e, type: 3}
  - layout: {fileID: 470820575514630869, guid: 8350bb0e530f4f847bc89e5a6414e355, type: 3}
    textA: There are those that refuse to be seen directly. You can feel their presence,
      but they remain unseen...
    textB: The lens holds them! It seems a camera is able to hurt them. Not all of
      them, only a select fewI have yet to test this on digital cameras. If the UV
      doesn't work, capture it on film.
    textC: 
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: -8853496014264632996, guid: b55209538fcd8394cb4322d22445aa83, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 2001516887877922869, guid: 9e3d2e1e33417724185301378553aee8, type: 3}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 3671605574920047432, guid: 781c553c4079c4141a3d7fd57a077ce1, type: 3}
    textA: I've seen the ghost of this woman, I tried to get a photo of her, but
      she was frightned and flew off. Could she possibly be one of the types that
      can be destroyed with a camera?
    textB: 
    textC: 
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: 7736703063926993187, guid: 47d5e17aa47863a4fb98d02a788b5c38, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: -1075207498280336613, guid: 49a8a794ef0e7fc4a82492eca8298e08, type: 3}
    imageC: {fileID: -8825618694164624126, guid: 5ae51f2fd0669d449a6084cfeacb6570, type: 3}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 4469434606004700145, guid: 13f5ebe6076bb59439d9876f37374a2e, type: 3}
    textA: Do not assume consistency.
    textB: 'They change

      They adapt'
    textC: They lie!
    textD: If the method fails, it was never the right one. Or it learned...
    imageA: {fileID: 935499960716218818, guid: 9b3b5521da93be64a9032e451f72eaf8, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 4370654923283873279, guid: e7e6a1ba164eda74f9a90732741b21b7, type: 3}
    textA: I remember seeing this guy around town, the clothes he wore are very similar
      to one of the ghosts I see often. Unlike the others, it seems to only come
      out at night. I have tried both other methods to defeat it but they did not
      work.
    textB: Could it be possible that the reason it comes out at night is not because
      of the UV, but because of the brightness? I must shine a torch at it to confirm!
    textC: It seems that some of the more recent ghosts have evolved compared to
      the older ones, the older methods don't seem to work on them, I must try my
      light theory soon.
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: -5009818906094167413, guid: ca7718e910cc25a41938dc94dadab29f, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: -8152136949519774684, guid: 0cea26b24b75432489a14a0adf447ba3, type: 3}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
